\par\pard\plain \tx1435\tx4306\li4306\fi-648\ri-6365\sl360\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Since infinity exists, it stands to reason that anything that can be imagined, exists in some other frame.  Advanced frame jumping is trying to be able to get to the point where the ability to imagine something, recognise that a frame exists somewhere that embodies this imagined universe, and then be able to jump there is what some believe to be the ultimate source of universal enlightenment. }
\par\pard\plain \tx1435\tx4306\li4306\fi-648\ri-6365\sl360\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Certain characters that go back in time and intentionally modify past event in an attempt to alter their current frame.  However, when they do it, their timeline changes from their perspective, but the rest of us in the original frame perceive them as winking out of existence. }
\par\pard\plain \tx1435\tx4306\li4306\fi-648\ri-6365\sl360\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Sometimes tech that was designed to work in the context of a certain frame does not work at all in a different one.  For example, a machine that was designed for use in a frame that has a fifth of the gravity that our does, would not work once exposed to different gravity, a different set of laws of physics, or direction of the flow of time. In fact, some things that work in one frame might be unsafe in another frame.  A sandwich that is made of antimatter (from an antimatter frame) might explode (or even better, maybe just cancel out) if drawn into a frame made up of matter. }
