\par\pard\plain \li4306\fi-648\ri-6365\sl360\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Characters }
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Monks Group of space travelling monks who are trying to bring the full universe to a state of complete enlightenment.  They are perceived as mysterious as their frame is difficult to comprehend from the perspective of the \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8216\'91normies\u8217\'92}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Criminal Group A group of criminals who have either mastered the ability to jump a limited amount of frames, or have a device that allows them to do so.  Their motivation is one of simple greed, and they often pull off inter-frame heists  This can be tricky though as the expected outcome is not always predictable because of the nature of some of the frames that they use. }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Art Dealers A group of art dealers who buy, sell, and fence stolen artworks.  They are shifty in that they are trying to manipulate the art market and the prices of certain works for their own gain.  They are occasionally robbed by the previous group, but have set up some elaborate defences.  }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Security Consultants (or arm of the art dealer cartel) that is analogous to digital security combating hackers.  Their perspective is always trying to combat and stay one step ahead of the art thieves.  The art thieves will occasionally try to get these guys to act as double agents. }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Hackers: Many individual Hackers are trying to test the boundaries of frame travel. Invent new ways of jumping frames, discover new kinds of frames that were previously hidden, discovering ways to detect stickers that were placed by someone else, and equally important, detect where they go.   Their motivation is simply one of exploration, and discovery, though they are not above selling their latest discovery if it means money, new tech, etc\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8230\'85  They are completely politically independent, oftentimes loners.}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Physicists:  As Quantum physics changed the way that people understood how the universe operates scientists splintered into different groups  Some began working for large corporate interests.   The ability to jump frames is only in its infancy on a commercial level, but has a huge impact on corporate interests by reinventing shipping and delivery.  There is some heavy math that needs to take place to use frame jumping to accurately materialize.  It is very dangerous as something can materialize in the middle of something or someone else. Other Physicists are exploring Buddhist thought once it became clear that the monks are clearly leveraging quantum properties in their very advanced navigation of frames. }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 SubPhysicists:  A group of people who aren\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92t necessarily scientists as they do not do any research into new ideas (although some might stumble upon new discoveries by accident).   These are the people who actually make the frame stickers.  They are usually much richer than actual physicists as they are typically selling to high bidders, the mob, etc\u8230\'85 There is a huge black market for sticker technology.  }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Terms}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Frame:  Derived from the expression \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8216\'91frame of reference\u8217\'92, a frame is basically a dimension.  Frames all coexist simultaneously, but follow possibly wildly different laws of physics, speed of how time progresses (including which direction that it flows in).  Based on the overlap of quantum physics and Buddhist thinking.  At the time of the story, understanding of frames, jumping frames, and how they behave, and what opportunities exist is only in its infancy. }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Personal Frame Of Reference: A timeline seen from a certain perspective.  For example, a person named Fred wakes up one morning, travels back in time,5 years, gets a bite to eat at that restaurant that had really great empanadas before going out of business shortly thereafter, then returns to the previous time frame. Fred experiences his timeline, as a linear progression.  However, his girlfriend Eloise who did not join him, has a different Personal Frame of Reference, because from her perspective, Fred was only gone for a few minutes, but upon returning was a few hours older. }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Frame Laws: Does there need to be some kind of governance in place for the authorities to police how people use frames?  For example, maybe it is illegal to use frame jumping in certain circumstances?  Explore this more}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Stickers:  Sticker is a catch all terms that means anything that can be used as a fixed portal between frames.  Oftentimes, they often embedded in actual stickers that are placed in certain places that allow someone to jump between two frames.  They can be embedded in a work of art, in a postal sticker that has been tagged to look like normal graffiti or vandalism.  They are usually hidden in plain sight.  As of yet, only a very few people possess the ability to detect Stickers that have placed by someone else. (Who makes stickers? Is it hackers, or physicists, or monks?)  It probably should be physicists}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Stickernet: Maybe some groups can create a network of stickers that has a central map of all the different \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8216\'91stops\u8217\'92 that are on the network (like a subway).  This would need to be more of a large organization (government, the mob, corporations, etc).  These would more likely be password protected, although some hackers might have been able to hack the PWs and steal access.  However, some of the stops might be guarded if the pop out at the wrong place.  }
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Term for modifying your own timeline:  There should be a concept of someone who modifies their own timeline.  It is likely to have unexpected consequences when it is all said and done.  In fact, maybe there are people who are somehow \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8216\'91marked\u8217\'92 that have done this.  Everyone else can tell as there is some kind of tell. }
